<item>
            <title>[HIVE-27408] Parquet file opened for reading stats is never closed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-27408</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ParquetRecordWriterWrapper while closing the writer tries to collect the stats by creating a reader (opening the file). But it never closes the reader (never closes the file). This can leave the file open hence consuming memory and associated file handle resources.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/io/parquet/write/ParquetRecordWriterWrapper.java#L143-L155&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/master/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/io/parquet/write/ParquetRecordWriterWrapper.java#L143-L155&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
